## ğŸ”’ Security and Best Practices

### 1. Secrets Management Rules
```yaml
security_rules:
  token_setup:
    - never: expose tokens in code or logs
    - always: use repository/organization secrets
    - suggest: environment-specific token naming
    - validate: token permissions and chat access
  
  data_privacy:
    - avoid: sensitive data in notifications (passwords, keys)
    - sanitize: error messages and logs
    - limit: information exposure in public repositories
```

### 2. Workflow Security
```yaml
workflow_security:
  permissions:
    - minimal: only required permissions for each job
    - secure: use specific action versions (@v3, not @main)
    - validate: third-party action usage
    - explicit: always declare permissions block when using GitHub API
  
  error_handling:
    - graceful: failure handling without breaking pipelines
    - informative: error messages without sensitive data
    - recoverable: continue-on-error for non-critical notifications
```

### 3. GitHub API Integration and Permissions

âš ï¸ **CRITICAL:** When generating workflow integrations that use GitHub API calls, ALWAYS include appropriate `permissions:` block.

#### ğŸ“‹ **Required Permissions by API Type:**

```yaml
# ğŸ” Repository monitoring and Actions API
permissions:
  contents: read        # âœ… Required - Basic repository access
  actions: read         # âœ… Required - For workflow runs API
  
# ğŸ› Issues monitoring  
permissions:
  contents: read        # âœ… Required - Basic repository access
  issues: read          # âœ… Required - For issues and comments API

# ğŸ”„ Pull Requests monitoring
permissions:
  contents: read        # âœ… Required - Basic repository access  
  pull-requests: read   # âœ… Required - For PRs and reviews API

# ğŸ“Š Complex monitoring (Issues + PRs + Actions)
permissions:
  contents: read        # âœ… Required - Basic repository access
  issues: read          # âœ… Required - For issues API
  pull-requests: read   # âœ… Required - For PRs API  
  actions: read         # âœ… Required - For workflow runs API
```

#### âœ… **Complete Workflow Example with Permissions:**

```yaml
name: ğŸ” GitHub Actions Monitoring
on:
  schedule:
    - cron: "0 */6 * * *"  # Every 6 hours
  workflow_dispatch:

jobs:
  monitor-workflows:
    name: ğŸ” Monitor GitHub Actions Health
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    permissions:
      contents: read      # âœ… Basic repository access
      actions: read       # âœ… For GitHub Actions API
    
    steps:
      - name: ğŸ“¥ Checkout repository
        uses: actions/checkout@v4
      
      - name: ğŸ“Š Analyze workflow runs  
        id: analysis
        run: |
          # Get recent workflow runs (using github.token, not secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN)
          recent_data=$(curl -s -H "Authorization: token ${{ github.token }}" \
            "https://api.github.com/repos/${{ github.repository }}/actions/runs?per_page=50")
          
          # Count failures in last 24 hours
          failures=$(echo "$recent_data" | jq --arg date "$(date -u -d '24 hours ago' '+%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ')" \
            '[.workflow_runs[] | select(.created_at >= $date and .conclusion == "failure")] | length')
          
          echo "failures=${failures:-0}" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT
      
      - name: ğŸ“¢ Send monitoring alert
        if: steps.analysis.outputs.failures > 2
        uses: asychin/telegram-notify-action@v3.1.0
        with:
          telegram_token: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN }}
          chat_id: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID }}
          template: warning
          template_vars: |
            {
              "customMessage": "âš ï¸ GitHub Actions Alert\\n\\nğŸš¨ Failed runs: ${{ steps.analysis.outputs.failures }}\\nğŸ·ï¸ Repository: ${{ github.repository }}\\nâ° Last 24 hours"
            }
```

#### ğŸš¨ **Common Permission Errors:**

```yaml
# âŒ WRONG - Missing permissions block
jobs:
  monitor:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    # Missing permissions block!
    steps:
      - run: curl -H "Authorization: token ${{ github.token }}" api.github.com/...
        # Will fail with 403 Forbidden

# âŒ WRONG - Using non-existent permission  
permissions:
  contents: read
  metadata: read        # âŒ ERROR: 'metadata' permission doesn't exist!

# âŒ WRONG - Missing required permission
permissions:
  contents: read        # âœ… OK
  # Missing 'actions: read' for workflow runs API
  
# âœ… CORRECT - Proper permissions
permissions:
  contents: read        # âœ… Basic access
  actions: read         # âœ… For workflow runs API
```

#### ğŸ”§ **API Troubleshooting:**

**Problem:** `HTTP 403 Forbidden` from GitHub API  
**Solution:** Add missing permissions to workflow job:
```yaml
permissions:
  contents: read
  actions: read         # Add this for workflow runs API
  issues: read          # Add this for issues API  
  pull-requests: read   # Add this for PRs API
```

**Problem:** `HTTP 404 Not Found` from Actions API  
**Solution:** Check if Actions are enabled in repository settings:
- Repository â†’ Settings â†’ Actions â†’ General
- Ensure "Actions permissions" allows workflow runs
- Check "Workflow permissions" has read access

## ğŸ”— GitHub Events Integration Patterns

### 1. Issues and Comments Monitoring

```yaml
name: ğŸ› Issues Notifications
on:
  issues:
    types: [opened, closed, reopened, assigned, labeled]
  issue_comment:
    types: [created, edited, deleted]

jobs:
  issue-notification:
    name: ğŸ“¢ Issue Activity Notification  
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    permissions:
      contents: read        # âœ… Basic repository access
      issues: read          # âœ… Required for issues API
    
    steps:
      - name: ğŸ“¢ Send Issue notification
        uses: asychin/telegram-notify-action@v3.1.0
        with:
          telegram_token: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN }}
          chat_id: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID }}
          message: |
            ğŸ› <b>Issue ${{ github.event.action }}</b>
            
            <b>ğŸ“‹ Title:</b> ${{ github.event.issue.title }}
            <b>ğŸ”— Issue:</b> #${{ github.event.issue.number }}
            <b>ğŸ‘¤ Author:</b> @${{ github.event.issue.user.login }}
            <b>ğŸ·ï¸ Repository:</b> ${{ github.repository }}
          inline_keyboard: |
            [
              [
                {"text": "ğŸ‘€ View Issue", "url": "${{ github.event.issue.html_url }}"},
                {"text": "ğŸ“ Comment", "url": "${{ github.event.issue.html_url }}#issuecomment-new"}
              ]
            ]
```

### 2. Pull Request Monitoring  

```yaml
name: ğŸ”” Pull Request Notifications
on:
  pull_request:
    types: [opened, closed, reopened, ready_for_review]
  pull_request_review:
    types: [submitted, edited, dismissed]

jobs:
  pr-notification:
    name: ğŸ“¢ PR Activity Notification
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    permissions:
      contents: read        # âœ… Basic repository access
      pull-requests: read   # âœ… Required for PRs API
    
    steps:
      - name: ğŸ“¢ Send PR notification
        uses: asychin/telegram-notify-action@v3.1.0
        with:
          telegram_token: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN }}
          chat_id: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID }}
