### **ğŸš¨ CRITICAL: Correct Integration Examples**

#### **âœ… CORRECT: Using Built-in Templates**
```yaml
# Deployment success with built-in template
- name: ğŸ“¢ Notify Deployment Success
  uses: asychin/telegram-notify-action@v3.1.0
  with:
    telegram_token: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN }}
    chat_id: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID }}
    template: deploy  # âœ… Built-in template
    template_vars: |  # âœ… JSON format with null safety
      {
        "customMessage": "Deployed to ${{ github.ref_name }}!",
        "deployStatus": "${{ job.status == 'success' && 'successful' || 'failed' }}"
      }
```

#### **âœ… CORRECT: Null-Safe template_vars**
```yaml
# âœ… CORRECT - All step outputs have fallbacks
- name: ğŸ“Š Get Statistics
  id: stats
  run: |
    # This step might fail and produce null outputs
    echo "total_runs=25" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT
    echo "success_runs=20" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT
    # failed_runs not set = null

- name: ğŸ“¢ Send Statistics Report
  uses: asychin/telegram-notify-action@v3.1.0
  with:
    telegram_token: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN }}
    chat_id: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID }}
    template: info
    template_vars: |
      {
        "customMessage": "ğŸ“Š Build Statistics Report",
        "totalRuns": "${{ steps.stats.outputs.total_runs || '0' }}",
        "successRuns": "${{ steps.stats.outputs.success_runs || '0' }}",
        "failedRuns": "${{ steps.stats.outputs.failed_runs || '0' }}",
        "successRate": "${{ steps.stats.outputs.success_rate || 'N/A' }}%"
      }
```

#### **âŒ WRONG: Null Values in template_vars**
```yaml
# âŒ WRONG - No fallback values
- name: ğŸ“¢ Send Statistics Report
  uses: asychin/telegram-notify-action@v3.1.0
  with:
    template: info
    template_vars: |
      {
        "customMessage": "ğŸ“Š Build Statistics Report",
        "totalRuns": "${{ steps.stats.outputs.total_runs }}",      # Could be null
        "successRuns": "${{ steps.stats.outputs.success_runs }}",  # Could be null
        "failedRuns": "${{ steps.stats.outputs.failed_runs }}"     # Could be null
      }
# Result: Template shows "Total Runs: null" instead of actual data
```

#### **âœ… CORRECT: Custom Message (No Template)**
```yaml
# Custom message without template
- name: ğŸ“¢ Send Custom Notification  
  uses: asychin/telegram-notify-action@v3.1.0
  with:
    telegram_token: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN }}
    chat_id: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID }}
    message: |  # âœ… Custom message, no template
      ğŸš€ <b>Custom Deployment Started</b>
      
      <b>Repository:</b> ${{ github.repository }}
      <b>Branch:</b> ${{ github.ref_name }}
      <b>Commit:</b> ${{ github.sha }}
```

#### **âœ… CORRECT: Progressive Notifications**
```yaml
# 1. Start notification with message_id capture
- name: ğŸ“¢ Start Notification
  id: start_notification
  uses: asychin/telegram-notify-action@v3.1.0
  with:
    telegram_token: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN }}
    chat_id: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID }}
    message: "ğŸš€ Deployment started..."

# 2. Update same message
- name: ğŸ“¢ Update Notification  
  uses: asychin/telegram-notify-action@v3.1.0
  with:
    telegram_token: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN }}
    chat_id: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID }}
    message_id: ${{ steps.start_notification.outputs.message_id }}
    message: "âœ… Deployment completed!"
```

#### **âœ… CORRECT: Scheduled Workflows with Custom Cron**
```yaml
# âœ… CORRECT: User said "every day at 12:00 except Friday and Saturday"
name: ğŸ“Š Daily Repository Report
on:
  schedule:
    # Daily at 12:00 UTC, Monday through Thursday (1-4)
    - cron: '0 12 * * 1-4'  
  workflow_dispatch: # Allow manual trigger

jobs:
  report:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
    - name: ğŸ“Š Send Repository Summary
      uses: asychin/telegram-notify-action@v3.1.0
      with:
        telegram_token: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN }}
        chat_id: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID }}
        template: info
        message: |
          ğŸ“Š **Daily Repository Summary**
          Repository: {{repository}}
          Period: Last 24 hours
```

```yaml  
# âœ… CORRECT: User said "every 6 hours but only during weekdays"
name: ğŸ” System Health Check
on:
  schedule:
    # Every 6 hours (6AM, 12PM, 6PM, 12AM UTC) on weekdays (1-5)
    - cron: '0 6,12,18,0 * * 1-5'
  workflow_dispatch:

jobs:
  health_check:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest 
    steps:
    - name: ğŸ” Health Check Notification
      uses: asychin/telegram-notify-action@v3.1.0
      with:
        telegram_token: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN }}
        chat_id: ${{ secrets.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID }}
