- ğŸ“‹ **Multi-file Fixes:** Fixed vulnerabilities in release.yml, monitoring.yml, test.yml workflows
- ğŸ”’ **ZERO VULNERABILITIES:** Achieved complete security compliance with automated verification

**CRITICAL SECURITY LESSONS FOR AI:**
âŒ **NEVER use:** GitHub variables like ${{github.event.release.body}} in heredoc contexts
âŒ **NEVER use:** GitHub variables like ${{github.repository}} in template_vars JSON
âŒ **NEVER use:** cat << EOF patterns with dynamic content from GitHub events
âŒ **NEVER mix:** {{template}} and ${{github}} variables in same JSON contexts

âœ… **ALWAYS use:** base64 encoding for dynamic content: echo '${{ toJSON(github.event.release.body) }}' | jq -r '.' | base64 -w 0
âœ… **ALWAYS use:** static text in template_vars: "customMessage": "Release published successfully"
âœ… **ALWAYS use:** printf or echo commands instead of heredoc for dynamic content
âœ… **ALWAYS use:** scripts/security-audit.sh to verify no vulnerabilities

